  "_comment": "OCSF 1.8.0 schema EXTENSION subset for the pipeline-normalization-fidelity bench (task #10). The C1 ocsf-mapping-fidelity benchmark ships schemas/ocsf/ocsf_1.8.0_subset.json covering five classes (authentication 3002, detection_finding 2004, network_activity 4001, dns_activity 4003, http_activity 4002). Two of THIS bench's four source classes — AWS CloudTrail -> API Activity (6003) and Sysmon process events -> Process Activity (1007) — are NOT in that C1 subset (api_activity is even listed there under other_classes_not_scored_here). This file adds exactly those two classes plus the one new referenced object (api), transcribed from the version-pinned OCSF 1.8.0 schema server (schema.ocsf.io/1.8.0/api/classes/{process_activity,api_activity} and .../objects/api) and the OCSF 1.8.0 release. The scorer MERGES this file ON TOP OF the C1 subset (same shape: classes{}, objects{}, catch_alls[]), so every existing object reference (process, actor, device, file, metadata, network_connection_info, user, session, ...) resolves through the C1 subset and is NOT re-transcribed here. A value of null means a scalar leaf; a string value is the name of the OCSF object the attribute references (resolved against the merged objects map; an object not transcribed in EITHER file is accepted as a 'deep' leaf by the C1 validator, exactly as in C1). Per-attribute requirement and data types are not reproduced (fidelity scoring does not use them); they live at schema.ocsf.io. See PROVENANCE.md. NOTHING IN C1's checked-in subset is edited by this bench.",
